Abuja (Sundiata Post) –  The Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC), Abia State Command has deployed 2000 men and officers of the agency to ensure security of lives and property during the Yuletide. The NSCDC State Commandant, Mr. Vincent Ogu, disclosed this while speaking on the preparedness of the agency ahead of the celebration. In a separate development, in Bauchi State, the police command has deployed over 3000 personnel across the state to secure churches and venues of events as part of security arrangements to ensure a free hitch Christmas and New Year celebration In a statement by its Public Relations Officer, DSP Ahmed Wakil, yesterday, he said it would collaborate with sister security agencies and all critical stakeholders to ensure that the celebration was peaceful and hitch-free. By Aminu Ahmed Garko   Minna   -    The Niger command of the Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC) has deployed 2,500 officers and men to ensure peaceful Christmas celebration in the state. Mr Philip Ayuba, the NSCC Commandant in the state, made this known on Monday in an interview… December 24, 2018 In "News" MINNA - The Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC) in Niger said it had deployed 253 personnel across the state to maintain law and order during the Eid-El-Kabir festival. The Commandant of the corps in the state, Mr Emanuel Ojeniyi, who made this known in an interview with the… October 3, 2014 In "News" ABUJA - The Nigeria Security and Civil Defence Corps (NSCDC) on Monday said it had deployed no fewer than 55,000 of its personnel nationwide to ensure a hitch-free Christmas and New Year celebrations. The NSCDC spokesman, Mr Emmanuel Okeh, told the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) in Abuja that about… December 22, 2014 In "News"